   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER TWO CONCERNING THE DIVINE TRINITY 2 Scripture Reading: Gen 1:1-2, 26; Matt 3:16-17; John 14:9-10; 2 Cor 3:17; John 8:16; Matt 27:46 OUTLINE Four crucial points concerning the Divine Trinity: The coexistence of the three: In the record of the Old Testament, the Father, the Son, and the Spirit being coexistent.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>In the record of the four Gospels, the Father, the Son, and the Spirit being coexistent.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>In the record of the Epistles, the Father, the Son, and the Spirit being coexistent.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The three the Father, the Son, and the Spirit being eternal.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The coinherence of the three.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The essential Trinity: The Holy Spirit as the essence of the conception of the Lord Jesus.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The Son coming from and with the Father, and the Father being always with the Son.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The Father being with the Son in the Son's crucifixion.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The economical Trinity.</S>
